article.headline: Canisius 75, Marist 49
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Frank Turner and Greg Logins each scored 16 points as Canisius defeated Marist 75-49 Friday. Julius Coles scored 15 and grabbed 11 rebounds while Tomas Vasquez-Simmons added another 13 points with 5 boards as Canisius (10-18, 4-13 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) won its third straight game. Ryan Schneider led Marist (9-21, 4-13 MAAC) with 12 points and 7 rebounds. The team shot just 32.1 percent, 18-of-56 for the game. A 25-2 run allowed Canisius to take a 38-18 lead at the break, their largest halftime lead and the fewest first-half points allowed by Canisius this season as well as Marist's lowest first-half output. Canisius shot 15-for-35 in the first half. The MAAC's top rebounding team, Canisius ruled the boards, out-rebounding Marist 46-27. Canisius followed in the second half shooting 50 percent (12-of-24).
